---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="FAQ" description="Frequently asked questions about me and my work.">
  <div class="py-12 md:py-20 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-12">
      Common questions about my work, thinking, and approach.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
      <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-bold text-lg hover:text-accent transition">
          <span>What's the focus of your writing?</span>
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          I write about first-principles thinking, productivity and workflow optimization, and what
          it takes to build things in public. My goal is to share mental models and frameworks that
          might be useful to others.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
      <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-bold text-lg hover:text-accent transition">
          <span>How often do you publish new posts?</span>
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          I aim for one substantive post per month, though the frequency varies based on what I'm
          working on. Quality over quantity is my approach—I'd rather publish one thoughtful post
          than multiple low-effort pieces.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
      <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-bold text-lg hover:text-accent transition">
          <span>Can I use your ideas or quotes?</span>
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Absolutely! If something resonates with you, feel free to use it, share it, or build on
          it. Just give attribution when possible. I believe ideas are meant to be shared and
          improved upon.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
      <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-bold text-lg hover:text-accent transition">
          <span>How can I contact you?</span>
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          The best way is to reach out on Twitter/X or LinkedIn. I try to respond to genuine messages
          and questions. You can find links in the footer of this site.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
      <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-bold text-lg hover:text-accent transition">
          <span>Do you take consulting or collaboration opportunities?</span>
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          I'm open to the right opportunities—whether that's writing projects, speaking engagements,
          or collaborations with people thinking about similar problems. Reach out with details about
          what you have in mind.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
      <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-bold text-lg hover:text-accent transition">
          <span>What tools do you use to build this site?</span>
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          This site is built with Astro, a modern static site builder, and styled with Tailwind CSS.
          Posts are written in Markdown. The source code practices the philosophy of simplicity and
          static generation—no databases or complex infrastructure needed.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
      <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-bold text-lg hover:text-accent transition">
          <span>Can I subscribe to your posts?</span>
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          Currently, the best way to stay updated is to follow me on Twitter/X or check back on the
          blog regularly. I'm considering adding an email newsletter in the future—follow me for
          announcements if that interests you.
        </p>
      </details>

      <!-- FAQ Item 8 -->
      <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 cursor-pointer">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between font-bold text-lg hover:text-accent transition">
          <span>What's your philosophy on productivity?</span>
          <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">▼</span>
        </summary>
        <p class="mt-4 text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          I believe productivity is about intentionality, not optimization. It's about understanding
          what actually matters to you and removing friction around those things. The best productivity
          tool is one that gets out of your way and lets you focus on what you care about.
        </p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  details summary {
    list-style: none;
  }

  details summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  details[open] summary span:last-child {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }
</style>
